            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "What's changed is: from Python 3.14 `wraps` will copy `__annotate__` (i.e. the function that generates annotations lazily) rather than `__annotations__`.\n\nWe don't yet support PEP 649 annotations (and it's are probably not likely to any time soon) so this function doesn't exist.\n\nI think it might be possible to implement a placeholder for `__annotate__` to support this use without having to do PEP 649 properly",
