            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thank you very much for the answer. For now I’m using a temporary solution: forcibly copying `__annotations__`.\n\n```python\ndef deco(func):\n    @wraps(func)\n    def wrapper(a: int, b: str):\n        print(222, get_type_hints(func))\n        return func(a, b)\n\n    wrapper.__annotations__ = func.__annotations__\n    return wrapper\n```\n\nI still hope that one day PEP 649 will be supported, but I know it’s very difficult to implement.",
